---

The following code does not compile.
```
module level2();
     logic [3:0] mem;
endmodule

module level1();
     level2 ul2();

     task doit(input logic [3:0] v);
         ul2.mem = v;
     endtask
endmodule


module level0();
     level1 ul1();
endmodule

```

The error message is:
```
%Error: Internal Error: taskscope.v:9: ../V3LinkDot.cpp:1372: Couldn't resolve inlined scope 'ul1' in: v.ul1

```

Changing the name of the tasks input variable to anything other than "v" fixes the problem.
